README

Libraries Used
1. pybaseball
2. sqlite3
3. BeautifulSoup
4. requests
5. numpy

Objective:
The following python program utilizes the aforementioned libraries to calculate the
qualifying offer for the year in the given data set. Additionlly, the program fetches
player statistics using pybaseball from the top 125 players by salary and outputs 
the available data to the console. A short summary of valuable players by WAR/salary
is included as well.

Instructions:
Download all files in the folder and be sure to install the necessary packages using 
pip3 install -r requirements.txt. From there, run the program from the commandline in 
your terminal using: python3 assessmentQ2.py

Resources:
1. https://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/bs4/doc/
2. https://www.dataquest.io/blog/web-scraping-python-using-beautiful-soup/
3. https://github.com/jldbc/pybaseball/tree/master/docs
4. https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.DataFrame.query.html

*Thank you to Zo Obradovic and the Phillies Baseball R+D Department for the opportunity and I hope to hear from you soon